article.description: Gerard Andrus had 20 points as Prairie View topped Alabama A&M 69-54 on Monday night.
article.headline: Andrus scores 20, sparks Prairie View past Alabama A&M 69-54
article.linkText: Andrus scores 20, sparks Prairie View past Alabama A&M 69-54
article.story: NORMAL, Ala. -- Gerard Andrus had 20 points as Prairie View topped Alabama A&M 69-54 on Monday night. Darius Williams had 12 points for Prairie View (11-11, 7-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Devonte Patterson added 12 points. The Bulldogs' 29.3 field goal percentage represented the worst mark by a Prairie View opponent this season. Garrett Hicks had 16 points for the Bulldogs (5-15, 2-7), who have now lost six games in a row. Cameron Alford added 14 points and six rebounds. Evan Wiley had seven rebounds. Prairie View takes on Texas Southern at home on Saturday. Alabama A&M takes on Arkansas-Pine Bluff on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
